Get a Name Cluster

Source: R/get_name_cluster.R
get_name_cluster.Rd

A `Name Cluster` is a character vector of all the unique labels associated with a concept, including labels derived from `Maps to` relationships from the Concept Relationship table.

get_name_cluster(
  concept_obj,
  vocab_schema = "omop_vocabulary",
  conn,
  conn_fun = "connectAthena()",
  cache_only = FALSE,
  skip_cache = FALSE,
  override_cache = FALSE,
  render_sql = TRUE,
  verbose = TRUE,
  sleepTime = 1
)

Arguments

concept_obj

May be an integer or a `concept` class object.

Examples

library(chariot)
library(tidyverse)

conn <- connectAthena()

#> Connecting using PostgreSQL driver
